### Test Agency Creation System
### Use this file with REST Client extension in VS Code or any HTTP client

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@adminEmail = admin@system.com
@adminPassword = admin123

### 1. Login as System Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{adminEmail}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}"
}

### Save the token from response and use it below
### Replace <ADMIN_TOKEN> with actual token

### 2. Create Agency 1 - Acme Corporation
POST {{baseUrl}}/agencies
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Acme Corporation",
  "email": "admin@acme.com",
  "password": "acme123",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "address": "123 Business Street, City",
  "gstNumber": "06AAAAA0000A1Z5",
  "panNumber": "AAAAA0000A",
  "userName": "Acme Admin"
}

### 3. Create Agency 2 - XYZ Industries
POST {{baseUrl}}/agencies
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "XYZ Industries",
  "email": "admin@xyz.com",
  "password": "xyz123",
  "phone": "9876543211",
  "address": "456 Industrial Ave, City",
  "gstNumber": "06BBBBB1111B2Z6",
  "panNumber": "BBBBB1111B",
  "userName": "XYZ Admin"
}

### 4. Create Agency 3 - Tech Solutions
POST {{baseUrl}}/agencies
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Tech Solutions",
  "email": "admin@techsolutions.com",
  "password": "tech123",
  "phone": "9876543212",
  "address": "789 Tech Park, City",
  "gstNumber": "06CCCCC2222C3Z7",
  "panNumber": "CCCCC2222C",
  "userName": "Tech Admin"
}

### 5. Get All Agencies
GET {{baseUrl}}/agencies
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>

### 6. Get Agency by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/agencies/1
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>

### 7. Update Agency
PUT {{baseUrl}}/agencies/1
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Acme Corporation Updated",
  "phone": "9876543299"
}

### 8. Update Agency Status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/agencies/1/status
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 9. Login as Agency 1 Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.com",
  "password": "acme123"
}

### Save the token from response
### Replace <AGENCY1_TOKEN> with actual token

### 10. Create Customer in Agency 1 Database
POST {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer <AGENCY1_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fname": "John",
  "lname": "Doe",
  "company_name": "Doe Enterprises",
  "cdisplay_name": "Doe Enterprises",
  "customer_email": "john@doe.com",
  "cmobile_phone": "9876543210"
}

### 11. Get Customers from Agency 1 Database
GET {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer <AGENCY1_TOKEN>

### 12. Login as Agency 2 Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@xyz.com",
  "password": "xyz123"
}

### Save the token from response
### Replace <AGENCY2_TOKEN> with actual token

### 13. Create Customer in Agency 2 Database
POST {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer <AGENCY2_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fname": "Jane",
  "lname": "Smith",
  "company_name": "Smith Industries",
  "cdisplay_name": "Smith Industries",
  "customer_email": "jane@smith.com",
  "cmobile_phone": "9876543211"
}

### 14. Get Customers from Agency 2 Database
### Should only see Jane Smith, NOT John Doe
GET {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer <AGENCY2_TOKEN>

### 15. Verify Data Isolation
### Login back as Agency 1 and check customers
### Should only see John Doe, NOT Jane Smith
GET {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer <AGENCY1_TOKEN>

### 16. Delete Agency (Soft Delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/agencies/3
Authorization: Bearer <ADMIN_TOKEN>

### Success! You've tested:
### ✅ Agency creation with automatic database setup
### ✅ Multiple agencies with separate databases
### ✅ Data isolation between agencies
### ✅ CRUD operations per agency
### ✅ Agency management by system admin
